HIV Prevalence Overview

![Alt text](/gh-pages/images/prototype2.png "Program Screenshot")


I Introduction

This is a N-tier web application based on Ruby on Rails that serves 
to visualize the HIV prevalence and its coorelated factors. The 
application is an interactive design based on Google Visualization 
APIs and javascript libraries. Users are able to interact with a 
Cholopleth Map page, a Line Chart page, a Bubble Chart page and a 
customized perferrence page embedded in this system. Google News, 
Google Youtube and Wikipedia APIs are also integrated. Users by 
interacting with this application will be informed of the current 
situations and trends of the global Hiv infection as well as impacts 
of related indicators.

II System Requirements

*  Supported Operating Systems: GNU/Linux, Microsoft Windows 7 64-
bit, Macintosh OS 64-bit
*  Recommended Server: Rails v3.2.0
*  Recommended Database: MongoDB v2.2.0 
*  Recommended Browser: Google Chrome v23.0, Firefox v16.0.2 (Please
make sure Javascript is enabled) NOTE: IE may not be supported
currently

III Deployment for Testing Puropose

*  Please ensure that 
     Ruby,
     Rails,
     RubyGem,
     MongoDB 
   is successfully installed and configured.
*  Unzip the project files to a local folder
*  Setup database:
     In a terminal, run "mongod"
*  Open a terminal and cd into a project folder, run "bundle"
   (bson_ext may fail in Windows cmd, please use MinGW instead)
*  Initialize database:
     run "rake db:seed"
     (if failed, use "bundle update" instad in last step.)
*  Open a new terminal, cd into project folder and run "rails server"
*  Test: 
     Open a new browser, input url "http://127.0.0.1:3000/"
*  For testing an administrator account, please login with username: 
"puconghan" and password: "administrator"
*  For testing a user account, please login with username: "test2" 
and password: "testtest"

